@page
@model dynamic
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Architecture";
}
<section class="page-header">
    <h1>Architecture & Design</h1>
    <p>A layered, modular architecture built for clarity, extensibility, and integration.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Layered Design</h2>
    <p>The engine is structured as a set of interoperable layers, separating policy definition, decision logic, workflows, observation, and integration. This separation allows each layer to evolve independently while preserving a coherent governance model.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Configuration Over Hard‑Coding</h2>
    <p>Governance structures are expressed as configurations and models rather than hard‑coded logic. This enables rapid adaptation to new regulations, organizational changes, and emerging governance domains.</p>
</section>

<section class="content-block">
    <h2>Integration‑First</h2>
    <p>COR is designed to sit alongside existing systems, not replace them. Through integration points, it can observe, guide, and constrain behavior across heterogeneous environments.</p>
</section>
